File: Jason Rohde during his appearance at the Stellenbosch Magistrate Court. JOHANNESBURG - The Supreme Court of Appeal has granted convicted murderer Jason Rohde bail of R200 000. Rohde was found guilty of killing his wife Susan three years ago. WATCH: Jason Rohde sentenced to 20 years According to his bail conditions, he is only allowed to reside in Lonehill or Green Point to conduct business. The Johannesburg Businessman was sentenced to 20 years in prison by Judge Gayaat Salie-Hlophe in August for murder. WATCH: Jason Rohde found guilty of murdering his wife The date for leave to appeal his conviction is yet to be set by the Supreme Court.